<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I just finished the book and absolutely loved it up til the last 10 pages or so....I hate that Sage made this choice and is now starting her relations<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I just finished the book and absolutely loved it up til the last 10 pages or so....I hate that Sage made this choice and is now starting her relationship with Leo with lies....big ones. She wasn't the most sympathetic character, carrying on with a married man, but I thought she was showing growth and then the ending happened. Grrr.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
